let _markdown = "\n\n## Restriction Enzyme Digestion\n\nAll 3C-based methods rely on restriction enzyme digestion to fragment chromatin.\n\n## Common Enzymes\n\n| Enzyme  | Recognition | Cut Frequency | Best For     |\n| ------- | ----------- | ------------- | ------------ |\n| MboI    | ^GATC       | \\~700bp       | Hi-C, HiChIP |\n| HindIII | A^AGCTT     | \\~4kb         | Hi-C         |\n| NcoI    | C^CATGG     | \\~4kb         | ChIA-PET     |\n\n## Generate Fragment Map\n\n```python\nfrom chr3d.utils import generate_restriction_map\n\nfrag_map = generate_restriction_map(\n    genome=\"hg38\",\n    enzyme=\"MboI\",\n    output=\"hg38_MboI_fragments.bed\"\n)\n```\n\n## Assign Reads to Fragments\n\n```python\nhic_frag = hic.assign_fragments(fragments=\"hg38_MboI_fragments.bed\")\n```\n\n## Quality Metrics\n\n* **Valid pairs:** 40-60%\n* **Self-circles:** \\<5%\n* **Dangling ends:** \\<10%\n* **Re-ligations:** \\<20%\n\nSee guides for detailed fragment analysis.\n";
