let _markdown = "\n\n## Quality Control Guidelines\n\nQuality control is critical for ensuring reliable results from chromatin conformation capture experiments.\n\n## Universal QC Metrics\n\n### Valid Pairs Percentage\n\n```python\nqc = data.qc_report()\nprint(f\"Valid pairs: {qc['valid_pairs_pct']:.1f}%\")\n```\n\n**Thresholds:**\n\n* **Hi-C:** >40% (good), 30-40% (acceptable)\n* **ChIA-PET:** >30% (good), 20-30% (acceptable)\n* **HiChIP:** >35% (good), 25-35% (acceptable)\n\n### Cis/Trans Ratio\n\nExpected values:\n\n* **Hi-C:** >4\n* **ChIA-PET:** >4 for CTCF\n* **HiChIP:** >5\n\n### Library Complexity\n\n* **>0.8:** Excellent\n* **0.6-0.8:** Good\n* **\\<0.6:** Over-sequenced\n\n## Protocol-Specific QC\n\n### Hi-C\n\n* Long-range % should be 40-50%\n* Distance decay follows power law\n\n### ChIA-PET\n\n* Linker efficiency >60% (good)\n* PET clusters median >3\n\n### HiChIP\n\n* Enrichment >5x (good)\n* Trans % \\<15%\n\nSee tutorials for detailed QC workflows.\n";
