let _markdown = "\n\n## Contact Matrix Generation\n\nContact matrices are the fundamental data structure for chromatin conformation analysis.\n\n## From Pairs to Matrix\n\n```python\nfrom chr3d import HiC\n\nhic = HiC.from_pairs(\"sample.pairs.gz\")\nmatrix = hic.to_matrix(resolution=10000, balance=False)\n```\n\n## Multi-Resolution Matrices\n\n```python\nhic.to_cooler(\n    output=\"sample.mcool\",\n    resolutions=[5000, 10000, 25000, 50000],\n    genome=\"hg38\"\n)\n```\n\n## Normalization\n\n```python\nhic_norm = hic.normalize(method=\"ICE\", max_iter=500)\n```\n\n## Export Formats\n\n* **Cooler (.cool, .mcool)** - Recommended\n* **Juicebox (.hic)** - For visualization\n* **Text formats** - For custom analysis\n\nSee tutorials for complete examples.\n";
